result.name: Pacific Coffee

reviews.text: I went on weekend. Not so crowded. Once construction finished at front of building, will be more comfortable place.
Coffee was fine. I had a sausage roll which was also OK. Overall a reasonable place to go for a coffee and a bite to eat.

Tables are wobbly so basically, so you order you 35HKD coffee, fix your table and then can wait another 5 minutes to get your drink.

Very poor loyalty program, with an app that unlogin as soon as your arrive in front of the cashier. Asking you for card number to login and a password you can hardly remember in such situations. Can't reset the password either most of the time. So technically, very bad and pissing off experience, compared to Starbucks loyalty program which works much better.

Contacted their customer service but weren't much helpful.
Good place for hea without much interruptions
Nice to just chill. Opens till late enough and just 5 min away from the wanchai expo centre with a scenic promenade.

reviews.text: Fantastic location and many places to visit
A top business building in Wanchai area located next to the Hong Kong Exhibition and Convention Centre
A good Carpark near the Wan Chai Pier
Clean and tidy, securities are helpful.

As the location is quite remote from Subway and main road, not many people visit here over weekend. If you visit Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center, then it is a good choose for food as it is close
